		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://wordcounter.net/blog/?p=2944#comment-49500</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://wordcounter.net/blog/2017/02/15/102944_how-many-words-chapter.html#comments/49157&quot;&gt;The Devil&lt;/a&gt;.

I have watched my twin finish entire novels he purchased in 4 hours. I read a novel 3 hours before a university exam and was the only student in my class to actually answer the essay for a 4.0 score. We both prefer chapters in the 8-10k range because we read at such a speed that we almost experience the books as movies. I also tend to write 10k chapters. I will generally go through 6 to 7 chapters of mine in a single night while proofreading and modifying the flow. Moral of the story, write however big you are comfortable, y&#039;know.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://wordcounter.net/blog/2017/02/15/102944_how-many-words-chapter.html#comments/49157">The Devil</a>.</p>
<p>I have watched my twin finish entire novels he purchased in 4 hours. I read a novel 3 hours before a university exam and was the only student in my class to actually answer the essay for a 4.0 score. We both prefer chapters in the 8-10k range because we read at such a speed that we almost experience the books as movies. I also tend to write 10k chapters. I will generally go through 6 to 7 chapters of mine in a single night while proofreading and modifying the flow. Moral of the story, write however big you are comfortable, y&#8217;know.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
